title: Grateful Dead Live at Kansas City Municipal Auditorium Arena on 1981-07-07
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues-> Bertha-> Dancin' In The Streets, Big Railroad Blues-> El Paso, To Lay Me Down, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Bird Song-> Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Women Are Smarter, Candyman, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Black Peter-> I Need A Miracle-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
This Is The Real Deal Folks !!! I've been waiting for an upgrade of this show for a few years now, and SirMick has provided a very competent and very much appreciated matrix.  The SBD is not overly vocal-saturated and the 60/40% mix is just exactly perfect.  And for some reason, it blends very well too.  Usually, AUDs and SBDs can be so different in clarity and dimension, you notice the separation in the mix.  In this matrix, with the SBD being a little softer in the capture, the separation is not there and the recording sounds more natural to me.  This is a very well produced production.  Thanks SirMick.  Nice job.

And in saying that, with this being a killer performance (as per my other Neumann KM-184 AUD review of this show, I am happy to give it the ol' GD "X" Factor seal of approval.  This is a hair-raiser kids.  Grab it while you can !!!
Sweetness I have to agree with the first review, this sounds like Municipal Auditorium, and it sounds very good indeed. A fine show.
- Good show overall; I just don't like it when they haste Eyes like they always did in this era.

Our memories are better than we have any right to expect  This Matrix is a Gem. Hadn’t heard this show before and the Minglewood>Bertha>Dancin’ opener gives you a taste what’s in store. Turn it on and tune in.
